						<div class="postbody">I think I have managed to design a mapper using two ICs which has software-controlled one screen mirroring (the same bit selects a 4K CHR ROM bank), up to 64K PRG RAM with 16K banks, and up to 1M PRG ROM and 16K banks, although you cannot use a different pattern table for tiles and sprites, and you might not be able to change the bank during rendering. (The ICs are three NAND gates and a eight-bit latch.) Can you please tell me if it works?</div>

					
